        <prompt>Which Constitutional amendment abolished slavery in the United States?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">13th Amendment</option>
            <option letter="b">14th Amendment</option>
            <option letter="c">15th Amendment</option>
            <option letter="d">16th Amendment</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The 13th Amendment, ratified in 1865, officially abolished slavery and involuntary servitude throughout the United States.</explanation>
