    <question>
        <prompt>What was the primary goal of the Black Codes enacted by Southern states in 1865-1866?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To protect African American voting rights</option>
            <option letter="b">To restrict African American freedom and maintain white control</option>
            <option letter="c">To promote racial equality</option>
            <option letter="d">To provide education to former slaves</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>Black Codes were laws passed by Southern states to restrict African Americans' freedoms and maintain white control through strict labor and social regulations.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>Which group opposed President Johnson's lenient Reconstruction policies?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Radical Republicans</option>
            <option letter="b">Southern Democrats</option>
            <option letter="c">Moderate Republicans</option>
            <option letter="d">Freedmen's Bureau officials</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Radical Republicans, led by figures like Thaddeus Stevens and Charles Sumner, strongly opposed Johnson's lenient policies toward the South and pushed for more stringent Reconstruction measures.</explanation>
